            .</p>
               <p>PETER THWAITES. I am a <rs id="t18280911-271-viclabel1392" type="occupation">bootmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-271-victim1503 t18280911-271-viclabel1392"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280911-271-crimeloc1393">Aylesbury-street, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-271-crimeloc1393" type="placeName" value="Aylesbury-street, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-271-crimeloc1393" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-271-off1390 t18280911-271-crimeloc1393"></join>; the prisoner was my <rs id="t18280911-271-deflabel1394" type="occupation">apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-271-defend1502 t18280911-271-deflabel1394"></join>. On the 17th of August, about two o'clock, he was leaving my shop with some dirty linen; I searched his bundle, and found a pair of child's double soled boots; I asked him how he came to put them there - he said he had an order for them on the Sunday before, from a neighbour, I think he said, next door to him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Had he not before that sold two pairs of boots and shoes to a gentleman? A. He never took but one pair from me, by coming and saying he wanted a pair for a gentleman. I did not want to get his indentures cancelled - it was not because he was an apprentice from a school, and the consent of the Trustees was wanting, that I did not have it done; I do not know Mr. Hudson; the prisoner said he had a pair of boots ordered from him, and he was taking them to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-271-person1504">
                  HARRIET 
                  THWAITES
               <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1504" type="surname" value="THWAITES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1504" type="given" value="HARRIET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1504" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's wife. I missed the boots from the stock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-271-person1505">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1505" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1505" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1505" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and took up the prisoner. I asked him how he came to take them, and what he meant to do with the money - he said to spend it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Was any one present at this conversation? A. Yes; it was in Mr. Thwaites' shop - he did not say he had got an order for them while I was there - I swore this before the Magistrate.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-271-person1506">
                  PETER 
                  THWAITES
               <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1506" type="surname" value="THWAITES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1506" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1506" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . When I opened the bundle he gave me the account I stated, and then I went for an officer - the officer came in the mean time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-271-person1507">
                  HARRIET 
                  THWAITES
               <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1507" type="surname" value="THWAITES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1507" type="given" value="HARRIET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-271-person1507" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He said he had got an order for them, and was going to take the money and spend it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Why did you not state that in your first examination? A. I was not called in at Hatton-garden; the officer has not been speaking to me since I went down - he was speaking, but not to me; I heard some one tell him to hold his tongue.</p>
               <p>
